# Stay aligned with `origin/main` at three checkpoints

Upstream is **`origin`** → `https://github.com/adampadobe/AEP-Orchestration-Lab.git`.

You MUST run a sync check at **all three** of these points — not just at the start of a session:

## Checkpoint 1 — Before substantive edits

```bash
git fetch origin
git status                 # confirm not behind origin/main
# If behind on main:
git pull --ff-only origin main
# If on a feature branch:
git rebase origin/main     # or merge origin/main into the feature branch
```

## Checkpoint 2 — IMMEDIATELY before `git push`

Even if you fetched at the start, a teammate may have pushed while you were working:

```bash
git fetch origin
git status                 # MUST show "Your branch is up to date with 'origin/main'"
# If now behind:
git pull --rebase origin main
# Re-run any tests/verifiers that the rebase may have invalidated.
```

Only `git push` once `git status` shows you are 0 behind.

## Checkpoint 3 — IMMEDIATELY before `firebase deploy`

This one is the most often forgotten and the most dangerous:

```bash
git fetch origin
git status                 # MUST show 0 behind
# If behind:
git pull --ff-only origin main
# Rebuild any built artefacts (e.g. `npm run build:edp`, `npm run build:eds-quickstart`)
# so the deploy includes the teammate's changes too.
```

**Why this matters:** `firebase deploy --only hosting` ships whatever is on YOUR local disk in `web/`. If a teammate pushes to `origin/main` between your `git push` and your `firebase deploy`, your deploy will silently overwrite their hosted assets — even though `git` itself stayed clean. Pulling at deploy time is the only protection.

For built sub-apps (`web/profile-viewer/eds-quickstart/`, `web/profile-viewer/experience-decisioning/`), pulling alone is not enough — you must also re-run the relevant `npm run build:*` after the pull so the freshly-pulled source rebuilds before deploy.

## When in doubt

If `git status` shows you are behind at any checkpoint, **stop**. Pull first. Resolve any conflicts. Re-run verifiers. Then proceed.
